cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper presents a new model for time series classification that uses binary stochastic hidden units to model latent structure in the data. The model is demonstrated to perform well on a variety of computer vision tasks, including facial expression and action recognition, suggesting that it is likely to be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
